<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0462" sponsor="Tiara Auxier" designation="HB" otherSponsor="David P. Hinkins" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0883" date="03-06-26" printDate="03-06 21:58" subVer="-2" minVer="2" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>8</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="07/01/2026"><seclist><sect action="E" src="code" buid="2" uid="C53F-2-S402.5_2026070120260701" sort="53F02 04020520260701" mtype="section" effdate="07/01/2026">53F-2-402.5</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="approp" buid="6" uid="APP2027" sort="UP0002027" mtype="uncod" effdate="07/01/2026"/><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="7" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="07/01/2026"/></seclist></aminfo><amendinfo level="1"/><aminfo anum="-1" effdate="07/01/2026"><seclist><sect action="E" src="code" buid="2" uid="C53F-2-S402.5_2026070120260701" sort="53F02 04020520260701" mtype="section" effdate="07/01/2026">53F-2-402.5</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="approp" buid="6" uid="APP2027" sort="UP0002027" mtype="uncod" effdate="07/01/2026"/><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="7" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="07/01/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">School Bus Internet Access</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Tiara Auxier</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: David P. Hinkins</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill creates a grant program to provide internet connectivity on school buses in rural <ln numlevel="1" lineno="6" slineno="0-6"/>school districts.</gd><hphead lineno="7">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">defines terms;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10" level="1">creates a grant program for rural school districts to install and operate internet <ln numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11"/>connectivity systems on school buses;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">establishes priority criteria for awarding grants;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13" level="1">allows districts to combine grant money with district funds;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14" level="1">requires grant recipients to commit to long-term operation of internet connectivity <ln numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15"/>systems; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16" level="1">requires the State Board of Education to make rules for grant administration.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17" display="normal">Money Appropriated in this Bill:<fy fy="2027" ltid="2" seq="2027" numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18"><ltcat ltid="3" seq="1">This bill appropriates <ltamt>$325,000</ltamt> in operating and capital budgets for fiscal year 2027, all of <ln numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19"/>which is from the various sources as detailed in this bill.</ltcat></fy></moni><oc numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20">Other Special Clauses:<ocl type="effdate" sort="2" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21">This bill provides a special effective date.</ocl></oc><sa numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="0-22">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saent numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="0-23"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="53F-2-402.5" src="code" uid="C53F-2-S402.5_2026070120260701" buid="2" sort="53F02 04020520260701" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="0-24"><bold>53F-2-402.5</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="25"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="0-26">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="2" num="53F-2-402.5" type="enact" src="code" uid="C53F-2-S402.5_2026070120260701" sort="53F02 04020520260701" numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-2" number="53F-2-402.5" type="enact"><secline lineno="27">Section 1. Section <bold>53F-2-402.5</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="28"><bold>53F-2-402.5<parens/>. Rural school district transportation grants.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="2-1" dnum="_-o:1-e" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="7" groupid="5" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this section:</amend><subsection ssid="2-10" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="151" groupid="9" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">"Eligible school" means a public school within a school district:</amend><subsection ssid="2-42" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-5" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="156" groupid="13" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">located in a county of the fourth, fifth, or sixth class, as defined in Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="17-50-501"><ln numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-6"/>17-50-501</xref>; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-43" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="161" groupid="17" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">with fewer than 3,000 students enrolled in the school district.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-47" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="180" groupid="30" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">"Rural school district" means a school district that operates one or more eligible <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-9"/>schools.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-48" dnum="_-o:2-e" numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-10" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="181" groupid="31" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">Subject to legislative appropriations, the state board shall distribute grant money to rural <ln numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-11"/>school districts to install and operate internet connectivity systems on school buses.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-49" dnum="_-o:3-e" numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-12" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="188" groupid="36" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">A rural school district may apply to the state board for a grant under this section.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-50" dnum="_-o:4-e" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-13" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1007" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(4)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="193" groupid="40" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">The state board may award a grant to a rural school district that:</amend><subsection ssid="2-52" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-14" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1008" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="203" groupid="48" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">submits an application in accordance with state board rule; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-53" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-15" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1009" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="208" groupid="52" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">agrees to the requirements in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-402.5(7)">(7)</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-54" dnum="_-o:5-e" numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-16" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1010" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(5)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="334" groupid="147" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">In awarding grants under this section, the state board shall give preference to rural <ln numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="1-17"/>school districts that do not currently have internet connectivity systems on school buses.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-93" dnum="_-o:6-e" numlevel="1" lineno="44" slineno="1-18" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1011" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(6)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="387" groupid="189" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">Notwithstanding Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-402.5(5)">(5)</xref>:</amend><subsection ssid="2-94" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="45" slineno="1-19" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1012" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="392" groupid="193" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">subject to legislative appropriations, the state board shall ensure each eligible rural <ln numlevel="1" lineno="46" slineno="1-20"/>school district receives funding for at least two school buses; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-84" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="47" slineno="1-21" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1013" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="341" groupid="152" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">the state board may not award a grant to a district in an amount that exceeds the total <ln numlevel="1" lineno="48" slineno="1-22"/>cost to:</amend><subsection ssid="2-85" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="49" slineno="1-23" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1014" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="346" groupid="156" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">retrofit two school buses with internet connectivity systems; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-86" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="50" slineno="1-24" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1015" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="351" groupid="160" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">pay for internet connectivity services for two school buses for one year.</amend></subsection></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-55" dnum="_-o:7-e" numlevel="1" lineno="51" slineno="1-25" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1016" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(7)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="216" groupid="58" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">A rural school district that receives a grant under this section shall:</amend><subsection ssid="2-56" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="52" slineno="1-26" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1017" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="221" groupid="62" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">use grant money to:</amend><subsection ssid="2-57" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="53" slineno="1-27" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1018" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="226" groupid="66" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">retrofit school buses with internet connectivity systems; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-58" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="54" slineno="1-28" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1019" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="231" groupid="70" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">provide internet access through a terrestrial wireless provider or a satellite <ln numlevel="1" lineno="55" slineno="1-29"/>internet service provider;</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-59" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="56" slineno="1-30" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1020" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="232" groupid="71" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">assume responsibility for the cost of internet connectivity services after the grant <ln numlevel="1" lineno="57" slineno="1-31"/>money for services described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-402.5(7)(a)(ii)">(7)(a)(ii)</xref> is expended;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-60" dnum="_-o:c-e" numlevel="1" lineno="58" slineno="1-32" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1021" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(c)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="238" groupid="75" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">maintain internet connectivity systems and services on the retrofitted school buses <ln numlevel="1" lineno="59" slineno="1-33"/>for at least three years after receiving the grant;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-61" dnum="_-o:d-e" numlevel="1" lineno="60" slineno="1-34" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1022" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(d)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="243" groupid="79" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">where applicable, coordinate with the Utah Education and Telehealth Network in the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="61" slineno="1-35"/>implementation and operation of internet connectivity systems;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-108" dnum="_-o:e-e" numlevel="1" lineno="62" slineno="1-36" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1023" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(e)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="465" groupid="252" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">ensure that internet connectivity provided on school buses under this section <ln numlevel="1" lineno="63" slineno="1-37"/>complies with the same content filtering and internet safety policies that apply to <ln numlevel="1" lineno="64" slineno="1-38"/>internet access in the district's school buildings; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-62" dnum="_-o:f-e" numlevel="1" lineno="65" slineno="1-39" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1024" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(f)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="248" groupid="83" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">comply with reporting requirements established by the state board in rule under <ln numlevel="1" lineno="66" slineno="1-40"/>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-402.5(10)">(10)</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-66" dnum="_-o:8-e" numlevel="1" lineno="67" slineno="1-41" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1025" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(8)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="393" groupid="194" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">A rural school district may:</amend><subsection ssid="2-95" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="68" slineno="1-42" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1026" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="398" groupid="198" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">use grant money awarded under this section in combination with the district's own <ln numlevel="1" lineno="69" slineno="1-43"/>funds to:</amend><subsection ssid="2-96" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="70" slineno="1-44" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1027" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="403" groupid="202" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">retrofit more than two school buses with internet connectivity systems; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-97" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="71" slineno="1-45" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1028" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="408" groupid="206" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">pay for more than one year of internet connectivity services for school buses; and</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-98" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="72" slineno="1-46" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1029" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="413" groupid="210" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">if the cost of internet connectivity systems and services is less than the grant award <ln numlevel="1" lineno="73" slineno="1-47"/>amount, use remaining grant funds to:</amend><subsection ssid="2-99" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="74" slineno="1-48" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1030" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="418" groupid="214" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" m-anum="0" m-ea="amend" m-pairid="526" m-groupid="307" m-style="1" m-owner="admin" m-level="1" amendtag="end">retrofit additional school buses with internet connectivity systems; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-100" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="75" slineno="1-49" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1031" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="423" groupid="218" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">pay for additional years of internet connectivity services.</amend></subsection></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-69" dnum="_-o:9-e" numlevel="1" lineno="76" slineno="1-50" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1032" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(9)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="278" groupid="103" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">If a grant recipient fails to maintain internet connectivity systems and services for the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="77" slineno="1-51"/>three-year period required under Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-402.5(7)(c)">(7)(c)</xref>, the state board may require the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="78" slineno="1-52"/>district to repay all or a portion of the grant money.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-70" dnum="_-o:10-e" numlevel="1" lineno="79" slineno="1-53" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1033" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(10)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="430" groupid="224" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">The state board shall make rules in accordance with Title 63G, Chapter 3, Utah <ln numlevel="1" lineno="80" slineno="1-54"/>Administrative Rulemaking Act, to implement this section, including rules that establish:</amend><subsection ssid="2-102" dnum="_-o:a-e" numlevel="1" lineno="81" slineno="1-55" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1034" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="435" groupid="228" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">the grant application process and timeline;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-103" dnum="_-o:b-e" numlevel="1" lineno="82" slineno="1-56" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1035" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="440" groupid="232" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">required elements of a grant application;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-104" dnum="_-o:c-e" numlevel="1" lineno="83" slineno="1-57" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1036" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(c)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="445" groupid="236" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">a methodology for determining:</amend><subsection ssid="2-106" dnum="_-o:i-e" numlevel="1" lineno="84" slineno="1-58" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1037" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="455" groupid="244" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">the total cost to retrofit two school buses with internet connectivity systems; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-107" dnum="_-o:ii-e" numlevel="1" lineno="85" slineno="1-59" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1038" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="460" groupid="248" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">the annual cost for internet connectivity services for two school buses for one <ln numlevel="1" lineno="86" slineno="1-60"/>year for purposes of the cap described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53F-2-402.5(6)(b)">(6)(b)</xref>; and</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="2-105" dnum="_-o:d-e" numlevel="1" lineno="87" slineno="1-61" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="admin" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1039" style="1" owner="e" level="1" amendtag="start">(d)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="450" groupid="240" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="end">reporting requirements for grant recipients.</amend></subsection></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="6" type="uncod" untype="approp" src="uncod" uid="APP2027" sort="UP0002027" langlock="false" pos="1" numlevel="1" lineno="88" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" nodeid="2" fy="2027" untype="approp" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="88">Section 2.  <bold>FY 2027 Appropriations.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="89"><summary numlevel="1" lineno="89" slineno="2-2">The following sums of money are appropriated for the fiscal year beginning July 1, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="90" slineno="2-3"/>2026, and ending June 30, 2027. These are additions to amounts previously appropriated for <ln numlevel="1" lineno="91" slineno="2-4"/>fiscal year 2027. </summary><licat nodeid="3" numlevel="1" lineno="92" slineno="2-5"><number>Subsection 2(a).</number><display display="true">Operating and Capital Budgets</display><summary numlevel="1" lineno="93" slineno="2-6">Under the terms and conditions of Title 63J, Chapter 1, Budgetary Procedures Act, the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="94" slineno="2-7"/>Legislature appropriates the following sums of money from the funds or accounts indicated for <ln numlevel="1" lineno="95" slineno="2-8"/>the use and support of the government of the state of Utah.</summary><committee nodeid="4" name="Public Education" seq="70"><display display="false">PUBLIC EDUCATION</display><agency nodeid="5" seq="29140000" name="State Board of Education"><display display="false">STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION</display><lineitem seq="29143000" nodeid="6" name="Contracted Initiatives and Grants" numlevel="1" lineno="96" slineno="2-9"><display display="true">ITEM 1</display><lidesc>State Board of Education - Contracted Initiatives and Grants</lidesc><sources><appsrc name="Public Education Economic Stabilization Restricted Account" srcid="8" seq="3030.1" onetime="true" numlevel="1" lineno="97" slineno="2-10"><display display="true">From Public Education Economic Stabilization <ln numlevel="1" lineno="98" slineno="2-11"/>Restricted Account, One-time</display><amt>325,000</amt></appsrc></sources><programs numlevel="1" lineno="99" slineno="2-12" display="true"><program name="Contracts and Grants" dstid="7" seq="29143008" numlevel="1" lineno="100" slineno="2-13"><display display="true">Contracts and Grants</display><pamt>325,000</pamt></program></programs><authorizations hide="true"/></lineitem></agency></committee></licat></sectionText></section></bsec><bsec buid="7" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="101" slineno="3-1" sn="3"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="101">Section 3.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="102"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="admin" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="7/1/2026">July 1, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>3-6-26 7:01 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>